subSubSection.paragraph:
A2 (Fig. 
8B
) with allobasis carrying 1 abexopodal seta on distal third. Exp absent. Enp with subapical row of spinules, and with 2 unipinnate and 1 bare seta distally on inner margin; apically with 6 setae, three of which geniculate, outermost seta very small.

Mxp (Fig. 
8C
) with syncoxa lacking a terminal seta, but with rounded row of spinules; basis with 2 rows of spinules; enp turned into claw as long as basis and accompanied by small seta.

P1 (Fig. 
9A
) with longitudinally prolonged coxa and basis, the latter carrying 1 outer bipinnate and 1 inner bare seta, the latter being displaced on anterior surface. Exp 3-segmented, slightly surpassing half of length of enp-1. Exp-1 with 1 outer bipinnate spine; exp-2 with 1 outer bare geniculate seta; exp-3 smallest, bearing 4 bare geniculate setae.

