subSubSection.paragraph:
P5 (Fig. 
9B
) with outer seta arising from long spinulose setophore; benp completely reduced, represented by 2 setae, one of which of fishbone pattern, the other seta bare. Additionally with 3 tube pores. Exp fused with baseoendopodal part, long and slender, laterally with 2 bare setae; subapically with 2 bipinnate setae and 1 tube pore; apically with 1 long bipinnate seta.

