subSubSection.paragraph:
P6/GF (Fig. 
8E
). P6 small, forming bilobate sclerotized structure in front of gonopore, each leg carrying 1 small bipinnate seta.

Habitus (Fig. 
7C
) slender, slightly smaller than female with a body length of about 560µm. Ornamentation of cphth and body somites very similar to that in female, with slight variation regarding DP I-DP IX.

